node.text: Welcome back to Food for Mood! Head to the link in our bio for the full recipe along with even more content from our collaboration – and don't miss out on your chance to redeem a one-month free trial of Headspace! #WFMxHeadspace These statements have not been evaluated by the FDA. Just in time for World Vegan Day, Chef Chloe Coscarelli showed us how to make a Vegan Pumpkin Marble Cake! It's the perfect addition to @chefchloe’s Vegan Meal for 2 -- available to order now on shop.wfm.com (link in bio!). Get the recipe for the cake below! #WFMxChefChloe #Sponsored

Vegan Pumpkin Marble Cake (Makes 1 loaf)
Ingredients: 
- 2 cups 365 All-Purpose Flour 
- 1 cup 365 Organic Cane Sugar 
- 1 teaspoon 365 Baking Powder
- 1 teaspoon sea salt
- ½ teaspoon 365 Baking Soda
- 1 tablespoon pumpkin pie spice
- 1 cup canned pumpkin puree (or sweet potato puree)
- 1 cup 365 unsweetened Coconut Cream, mixed well before measuring
- ½ cup 365 Organic Coconut Oil, melted
- 1 tablespoon apple cider vinegar 
- 1 tablespoon pure vanilla extract
- 3 tablespoons unsweetened cocoa powder
- ½ cup vegan chocolate chips (optional)
- 365 Non-Dairy Plant-Based whipped cream or powdered sugar, for topping

Instructions:
Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Lightly grease a large loaf pan and/or line with parchment. 

Whisk flour, sugar, baking powder, salt, baking soda, and pumpkin pie spice. In another bowl, whisk together pumpkin puree, coconut cream, coconut oil, vinegar, and vanilla. Pour the wet mixture into the dry mixture and whisk until just combined (don’t overmix!). 

Transfer ½ cup batter into a small bowl and stir in cocoa powder and 2 tablespoons water until incorporated. 

Fill the prepared pan with alternating dollops of pumpkin batter and chocolate batter. Sprinkle in chocolate chips, if using. Using a thin knife or chopstick, gently swirl the chocolate batter into the pumpkin batter. Bake for ~60 minutes. Let cool and slice. Top each slice with 365 by Whole Foods Market Non-Dairy Whipped Cream or powdered sugar.

node.text: Prost! Oktoberfest season is right around the corner. Our friends at @olympiaprovisions shared their best tips on how to celebrate, including their limited-time, Whole Foods Market exclusive sausages. What’s your favorite sausage pairing? 🥨🍻*Please drink responsibly. Must be 21+.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on September 16, 2021. May be an image of outdoors.

node.text: It’s technically still summer, but mentally we’re here...

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Whole Foods Market on September 15, 2021 tagging @toastedtable. May be an image of food.

node.text: Calling all toast lovers 🗣 @toastedtable’s 🔥🍋🌱 recipe brings the heat, citrus and mint combination you didn't know you needed. Head to their page for the details. #wholefoodsmarket.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on September 13, 2021. May be an image of fruit.

node.text: Peak-season 🍇  have arrived. From juicy Gum Drops to sweet, fan-favorite Cotton Candy, we have them by the bunches. Comment 👇 with your guess on how many grapes are in these bunches.  #wholefoodsmarket #freshproduce #grapes #seasonaleating

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on September 10, 2021. May be an image of gelato and icecream.

node.text: First scoops of the crowd-voted #WFMNewScoop flavor have arrived, and we like what we're tasting! Head to our stories to see how we’re working to bring this celebration-worthy frozen treat to a freezer near you in April. 🎂 #wholefoodsmarket #icecream #dairyfree

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on September 09, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: Whether you're hosting for your home team or tailgating in rival territory this week, head to our Stories to scout the 🏈 Game Day Catering Menu full of fan favorites and all-vegan options. Please drink responsibly. #wholefoodsmarket #gameday #catering

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Whole Foods Market on September 02, 2021 tagging @lastingredient. May be an image of pizza.

node.text: @lastingredient has mastered the at-home pizza game with this balsamic mushroom, corn and garlic topped pie. Head to our Stories for expert tips to perfect your own 🍕 skills. #wholefoodsmarket #pizza #simplerecipes

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on September 01, 2021. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: What’s the first thing you put in your basket…and why is it the 365 Oat-Based Whipped Topping? #wholefoodsmarket

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Whole Foods Market on August 27, 2021 tagging @kalememaybe. May be an image of food and indoor.

node.text: This chickpea salad tossed in red wine vinegar and the oil from ☀️ dried tomatoes. That's all. Head to @kalememaybe's page for the recipe. #wholefoodsmarket

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on August 26, 2021. May be an image of drink, indoor and text that says 'WHOLE FOODS MARKET'.

node.text: We blinked and now pumpkin spice cold brew is back at our coffee bars. #wholefoodsmarket

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Whole Foods Market on August 25, 2021. May be an image of 1 person and indoor.

node.text: We ban high-fructose corn syrup, artificial sweeteners like aspartame and 150+ more ingredients from all the food we sell. That means more snack-time delight for team member Morgan and her son, Major. (Photo taken prior to current CDC guidance) So, parents, what’s one item your kiddo picks out at Whole Foods Market that you can always get on board with? Tell us in the comments 👇
